"title": "4496: perfume",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4496: perfume",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Substances used to make perfumes</h2>\n<h3>By blending ingredients</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:23-Exod30:24\">EXO 30:23–30:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:34\">EXO 30:34</a></p>\n<h3>Substances used as perfumes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:13-Song4:14\">SNG 4:13–4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:12-Song1:14\">SNG 1:12–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:6\">SNG 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:13\">SNG 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:3\">JHN 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Perfume ingredients as traded commodities</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:25\">GEN 37:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:19\">EZK 27:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:13\">REV 18:13</a></p>\n<h2>The attractive fragrance of perfume</h2>\n<h3>Its tempting allure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:17\">PRO 7:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:9\">ISA 57:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:40-Ezek23:41\">EZK 23:40–23:41</a></p>\n<h3>Its pleasing fragrance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:9\">PRO 27:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:3\">SNG 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:10\">SNG 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Fragrance used metaphorically</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:14-2Cor2:16\">2CO 2:14–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:2\">EPH 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:18\">PHP 4:18</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the use of perfume</h2>\n<h3>As a cosmetic</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:12\">EST 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:3\">RUT 3:3</a></p>\n<h3>To give fragrance to clothes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:8\">PSA 45:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:11\">SNG 4:11</a></p>\n<h3>In burying the dead</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:12\">MAT 26:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:8\">MRK 14:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:14\">2CH 16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:1\">MRK 16:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:56-Luke24:1\">LUK 23:56–24:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:7\">JHN 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:39-John19:40\">JHN 19:39–19:40</a></p>\n<h2>Perfumers</h2>\n<h3>Commissioned to make oil and incense for the sanctuary</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:29\">EXO 37:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25\">EXO 30:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:33\">EXO 30:33</a> <em>The manufacture of the sacred anointing oil by unauthorised persons was forbidden</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:35\">EXO 30:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:30\">1CH 9:30</a></p>\n<h3>Other references to perfumers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:13\">1SA 8:13</a> <em>perfumers in the service of the king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:8\">NEH 3:8</a> <em>Hananiah</em></p>",
